      "content": "Nationalism is a profoundly double-edged sword, and its inherent danger lies in its extreme forms. While a degree of shared national identity is necessary for social cohesion, when nationalism morphs into chauvinism or ethno-nationalism, it becomes a dangerous ideology that justifies exclusion and conflict. Therefore, it is not inherently good or bad, but rather a powerful tool whose application determines whether it builds community or fuels division.",
